Finally, in yellow what is really important to us is our deferred tax asset. And for those of you who haven\xe2\x80\x99t followed AIG that closely that the deferred tax asset for us is a very valuable source of free cash flow. And so, while there\xe2\x80\x99s been a lot of dialogue around changes in tax policy and it\xe2\x80\x99s still very preliminary at our investor day we did highlight some preliminary analysis. I think the key message is that we feel a reduction in the statutory tax rate is a positive for intrinsic value and a walk through why. First, for us we still believe that we\xe2\x80\x99re utilizing full all our foreign tax credits. So those will shield the higher amount of taxable income, which is very important.
Secondly, as you reduce the statutory tax rate, if there were an immediate reduction to 25% that would be approximately a 90 basis point increase in our return on equity. If it were to be an immediate reduction to 20%, that would be an increase in our normalized return on equity about 150 basis points. So we feel given where we are in the tax basis that that would close our gap on an ROE sense to peers.
Finally, clearly if we were to reduce the overall statutory tax rate as a function of tax policy, we did highlight that that would result in a re-measurement of our DTA, so an immediate reduction to 25% would result in a $4 billion re-measurement of our deferred tax asset associated with our NOLs and our timing differences and a reduction to 20% would be about $6 billion with respect to a re-measurement of those NOLs and the timing difference DTA.
So, that is in punch line a summary of how we think about valuing the company. If I turn the page and focus on the operating portfolio, here I leave you with a couple of messages. We have been extremely focussed on improving the overall return on equity of the operating portfolio and feel we\xe2\x80\x99ve improved it by about 150 basis points year-on-year. This has largely been a function of three things, improving our risk margins, our operating efficiency and capital management.
